  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200°C/ 180°C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Cut your <strong>sweet potato[es] </strong>(skins on) into wedges</p><p>Add the <strong>wedges</strong> to a large baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> and give everything a good mix up</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until the wedges are tender and starting to crisp</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1681209083446-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1681209083446-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1681209083446-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1681209083446-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-1-1681209083446-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, chop your <strong>parsley</strong> and <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks</p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong>, then peel and finely chop your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Add the <strong>chopped herbs, garlic</strong>, <strong>shallot</strong>,<strong> dried oregano</strong>,<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!) and 1 tbsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tbsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil </strong>to a <strong>pestle & mortar</strong> and grind everything to form a smooth paste</p><p>Tip: No pestle & mortar? Pulse in a food processor!</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1681209087222-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1681209087222-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1681209087222-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1681209087222-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-2-1681209087222-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Combine the <strong>paste</strong> with your<strong> red wine vinegar </strong>and <strong>mayo</strong> – this is your <strong>chimichurri mayo</strong></p><p>Slice your<strong> tomato[es]</strong> as thinly as you can</p><p>Slice your <strong>halloumi</strong> in half lengthways (where the natural crease forms)</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1681209090894-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/Step-3-1681209090894-x400.jpg",
